<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is a Florida man who spent 2021-2022</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">launching special purpose acquisition =
companies,</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">raising money from inve=
stors for the SPACs,</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">stealing the =
money, and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">losing it by day-tradin=
g meme stocks and crypto?</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He really covered all of the bases of 2021-202=
2 financial markets. He did SPACs to YOLO crypto and meme stocks, with some=
 accounting fraud and a touch of Ponzi. I don=E2=80=99t think there is any =
Elon Musk connection but otherwise this is maybe the most Money Stuff story=
 I have ever mentioned in Money Stuff.=C2=A0Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30154092.261520/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuan=
VzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByL2Zvcm1lci1jaGllZi1maW5hbmNpYWwtb2ZmaWNlci10d=
28tc3BhY3MtcGxlYWRzLWd1aWx0eS1mcmF1ZC1zY2hlbWU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBef5=
9fd24" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> how federal prosecutors tell it</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">COOPER MORGENTHAU, the former chief financial =
officer of two special purpose acquisition companies (=E2=80=9CSPAC-1=E2=80=
=9D and =E2=80=9CSPAC-2=E2=80=9D), pled guilty to one count of wire fraud i=
n connection with a scheme to embezzle more than $5 million from the two co=
mpanies. =C2=A0=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Between in or about June 2021 and in or about =
August 2022, MORGENTHAU, who was the CFO of SPAC-1 and SPAC-2, embezzled mo=
re than $5 million from the two companies. =C2=A0 SPAC-1 had recently had i=
ts initial public offering, while SPAC-2 was raising money from private inv=
estors in preparation for its anticipated IPO. =C2=A0MORGENTHAU used the em=
bezzled funds to trade equities and options of so-called =E2=80=9Cmeme stoc=
ks=E2=80=9D and cryptocurrencies, losing almost all of the money that he st=
ole. =C2=A0To conceal and facilitate his embezzlement from SPAC-1, MORGENTH=
AU fabricated bank statements, which he provided to SPAC-1=E2=80=99s accoun=
tant and auditor; made and caused to be made material misstatements in SPAC=
-1=E2=80=99s public filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission (=
=E2=80=9CSEC=E2=80=9D); and transferred some of SPAC-2=E2=80=99s funds to S=
PAC-1 to cover up the funds he had misappropriated from SPAC-1.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">COOPER MORGENTHAU, the defendant, =
used the funds that he embezzled from SPAC- 1 in or about June 2021 to trad=
e securities in his personal brokerage accounts, including options and equi=
ties of what are commonly called "meme stocks " like AMC Entertainment Hold=
ings, Inc.,=C2=A0GameStop Corp., and Clover Health Investments=C2=A0Corp. M=
ORGENTHAU=E2=80=99s trading resulted in losses of over approximately $1 mil=
lion, all of the money he had embezzled that month.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ah. Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/30154092.261520/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3By=
ZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0x/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB61a645cd" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the Se=
curities and Exchange Commission=E2=80=99s version</a>, which names the SPA=
Cs; the public one is African Gold Acquisition Corp., which is still huntin=
g for an acquisition.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a> I suppose it will make you feel better about the SPAC structure to lea=
rn Morgenthau <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3015=
4092.261520/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMy9=
jb21wLXByMjAyMy0xLnBkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe614d87b" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> was=C2=
=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>able to steal</a> the money that African Gold raised f=
rom public investors, just the other money:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">African Gold=E2=80=99s stock began trading pub=
licly on the New York Stock Exchange on February 26, 2021. Its initial publ=
ic offering of securities raised approximately $414 million from investors,=
 all of which was placed in a trust account to which Morgenthau did not hav=
e access. But Morgenthau did have access to African Gold=E2=80=99s operatin=
g bank account, which immediately after the initial public offering of secu=
rities, held approximately $1.5 million. This money was intended to fund Af=
rican Gold=E2=80=99s efforts to identify and acquire a company in the gold =
mining industry. As African Gold=E2=80=99s CFO, Morgenthau had authority to=
 make deposits into and withdrawals from this bank account to further Afric=
an Gold=E2=80=99s efforts to acquire such a company.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On June 4, 2021, Morgenthau transferred $36,70=
0 from the African Gold operating bank account to one of his personal broke=
rage accounts to fund trading in meme stocks. Similarly, on June 15, 2021, =
Morgenthau transferred $25,000 from the African Gold operating bank account=
 to his own checking account for personal expenses wholly unrelated to Afri=
can Gold. These were the first in a series of 34 withdrawals that Morgentha=
u made during June and July 2021, each below a $50,000 threshold that would=
 have triggered secondary review and approval by an African Gold board memb=
er. In all, Morgenthau transferred more than $1.2 million during this time =
to his personal bank and brokerage accounts, leaving African Gold with just=
 $100 in its operating bank account by July 29, 2021.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then he launched some new SPACs to raise m=
oney to cover up the money he stole from his old SPAC, and also to blow on =
crypto trading:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To cover his losses, Morgenthau raised money b=
y soliciting investors to help launch another series of SPACs: Strategic Me=
tals Acquisition Corp. I and Strategic Metals Acquisition Corp. II (togethe=
r, =E2=80=9CStrategic Metals=E2=80=9D). From at least July 2021 through at =
least July 2022, Morgenthau raised approximately $4.7 million from investor=
s in Strategic Metals, all of which he misappropriated for himself.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Morgenthau deposited some of the money he rais=
ed for Strategic Metals into African Gold=E2=80=99s bank account in order t=
o conceal his embezzlement from African Gold and its accountants and audito=
r. For example, Morgenthau deposited more than half a million dollars of=C2=
=A0Strategic Metals=E2=80=99 funds into African Gold=E2=80=99s bank account=
 on December 31, 2021, because he knew that African Gold=E2=80=99s auditor =
would confirm the account balance as of that date, in connection with Afric=
an Gold=E2=80=99s year-end audit. Almost immediately thereafter, Morgenthau=
 began withdrawing the money from African Gold=E2=80=99s bank account and u=
sed most of it to trade crypto asset securities.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just living 2021 to the fullest.</p>
